==Flowers (1980)==
Flowers were formed in Sydney in 1977 by [[Iva Davies]] ([[singing|vocals]], [[guitar]], [[bass guitar]], [[keyboard instrument|keyboards]], [[oboe]]), a classically trained musician, and their main creative force; with [[bass guitar|bass]] player Keith Welsh.<ref name="McF"/> Davies was working as a part-time cleaner at a squash court managed by Welsh's mother, they lived nearby and were both interested in forming a band.<ref name="Kruger">{{cite news |url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/music/songlines/2005/11/01/1130720527778.html |title=City Songlines |last=Kruger |first=Debbie |newspaper=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |date=2005-11-02 |access-date=2008-06-21 }}</ref> Additional musicians used by Flowers in 1978 were Anthony Smith on keyboards and Don Brown on [[Drum kit|drums]].<ref name="ARDb"/>
